    "justification": "Three conjuncts: (1) absolute partial rho > 0.1 establishes a non-trivial GC-independent signal; (2) sign must be positive — SINEs predicted to enrich expression via Alu-exonization / enhancer-co-option literature; (3) p threshold is a sanity backstop given genome-wide n.",
    "failure_mode": "If sign flipped or |partial rho| fell below 0.1, the SINE-as-expression-promoting framing would be falsified and the LTR sibling claim would lose its opposite-sign companion."
